bilingual.target: 那是保罗的儿子和女儿。

bilingual.source: She was the daughter of a local farmer.
bilingual.target: 她是当地一个农民的女儿。

bilingual.source: This is your brother or sister's daughter.
bilingual.target: 这是你兄弟或姐妹的女儿。

bilingual.source: Chen took out a large loan to cure her daughter.
bilingual.target: 陈贷了一大笔款来治愈她的女儿。

bilingual.source: "See," said the man to his wife, "our daughter."
bilingual.target: “看，”男人对他的妻子说，“我们的女儿。”

bilingual.source: The little girl who is wearing a Snow White costume is my daughter.
bilingual.target: 穿白雪公主服装的小女孩是我的女儿。

bilingual.source: "I'm sure I have seen her before," Hutun whispered to her daughter.
bilingual.target: “我确定以前见过她，”胡顿对她的女儿低声说。

bilingual.source: My five-year-old daughter can draw a beautiful picture in five minutes.
bilingual.target: 我五岁的女儿能在五分钟之内画出一幅漂亮的图画。

list.abstract: daughter（英 [ˈdɔːtə]，美 [ˈdɔːtər]），英语单词，名词，意思为女儿；雌性后代；女性后裔。短语搭配有daughter cell（子细胞），例句为“Because he lied to his daughter.（因为他对女儿撒谎了）”。 daughter名词类近义词有girl、dau，相关反义词有son、boy，复数形式为daughters。
《女儿》是具惠善继执导电影《妖术》、《桃树》后的第三部作品，也是自导自演的首部电影，从开拍之初就受到了大家的关注。尤其是具惠善用独特的叙述视角和突出的影像美构建的作品世界，让观众们充满了好奇与期待。 该片讲述对女儿强制体罚的母亲和承受着苦痛的女儿之间严重代沟的故事。通过成为初中生的“山（具惠善）”和想通过体罚控制自己女儿的“妈妈”（沈惠珍）之间的矛盾讲述社会问题。

yingyinNormal.en: Rosie had a daughter, and her daughter had my mom.
yingyinNormal.zh: 罗茜有个女儿，她的女儿生了我的妈妈。

yingyinNormal.en: Zoe zebra the postman's daughter.
yingyinNormal.zh: 邮递员的女儿斑马佐伊。

yingyinNormal.en: I do. I have a daughter. I have feelings.
yingyinNormal.zh: 真的，我有个女儿，我也有感情。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm his daughter. I'm Alice Kingsleigh.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我是他的女儿，我叫爱丽丝·金斯利。

yingyinNormal.en: I don't like you going out with my daughter Ross.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不喜欢你跟我女儿交往。

yingyinNormal.en: I didn't know her. I didn't know my daughter.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不了解她。我不了解我的女儿。

yingyinNormal.en: Your daughter, I suppose she talks and eats and everything?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你女儿一切都好吧？

yingyinNormal.en: Someone like me. Someone like my daughter.
yingyinNormal.zh: 像我一样的人，比如... 我女儿。

yingyinNormal.en: And your daughter, what's her name? Chloe. Chloe.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你女儿，她叫什么名字？克洛伊。克洛伊。

yingyinNormal.en: Guys, a daughter asks her father, "What's my thing?"
yingyinNormal.zh: 同学们，一个女儿问他爸爸，"我该做什么"？

yingyinNormal.en: See? A master. Merv, meet my daughter Haley.
yingyinNormal.zh: 瞧见没，大师。梅尔夫，这是我女儿海莉。很高兴见到你。

yingyinNormal.en: You're not covering for your daughter, are you, Mrs. Sachs?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你不是在给你的女儿打掩护的把，萨克斯夫人？

yingyinNormal.en: And her daughter. And her friends! Yeah, that's right.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还有女服务员的女儿。还有她的朋友们！是啊，没错。

yingyinNormal.en: Mr. Crouse. Mrs. Florrick. You could've knocked. My daughter's home.
yingyinNormal.zh: 克劳斯先生。福瑞克夫人。你可以敲门的，我女儿在家。

yingyinNormal.en: One daughter, the heiress of Rosings and very extensive property.
yingyinNormal.zh: 她只有一个女儿，也就是罗新斯的继承人，将来可以继承到非常大的一笔遗产呢。

yingyinNormal.en: My daughter has returned.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我女儿回来啦。

yingyinNormal.en: For a time you had that same will as you fought by my side. Daughter. I'm not your daughter.
yingyinNormal.zh: 曾经你也有那样的意愿与我一同战斗。女儿。我不是你的女儿。

yingyinNormal.en: And in the end, I will see my wife and daughter again.
yingyinNormal.zh: 到最后，我会再见到太太和女儿。

yingyinNormal.en: You followed the light. My daughter is a lot like you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你跟随着光明，我女儿真的很像你。

yingyinNormal.en: Yes. Actually, I am saying that. My daughter is no thief.
yingyinNormal.zh: 没错，就是这样，我女儿不是贼。

examination_example.sentence: On one side are white parents like Catherine Foley, a former president of the Parent-Teacher-Student Association at her <highlight>daughter's</highlight> middle school, who has come to see the district's increasingly pressured atmosphere as opposed to learning.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一方是像凯瑟琳·福利这样的白人家长，她曾在女儿所在的中学担任家长——教师——学生协会主席。她认为，该学区日益紧张的氛围不利于孩子们学习。

examination_example.sentence: But nobody greeted the <highlight>daughter</highlight> and mother when they arrived, though the visit has been planned.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但是当他们到达时，没有人向女儿和母亲打招呼，尽管这是已经计划好了的参观。

examination_example.sentence: The <highlight>daughter</highlight> feared her mother would be ignored there, and so she decided to move her into a more welcoming facility.
